gomodel:SYNGO_1827  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.9 PTPδ induces postsynaptic differentiation through IL-1RAcPb (shown with PTPδA3-ECD-Fc beads on neurons of wild-type (Il1rap+/+) and IL-1RAcP knock-out (Il1rap-/-) mice)\n\n3/11/2017 Pim\n- The role of IL-1RAcPb is studied via a Il1rap KO animal and rescue with overexpression of IL-1RAcP or IL-1RAcPb. Only IL-1RAcPb was able to rescue the phenotype of defective postsynaptic differentiation.. Experimental description: - Cells are of mouse species: \"Cell cultures, transfection, and coculture assay. Primary cortical cultures were prepared from mice at postnatal day 0 (P0) essentially as described previously\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1827" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

